In England, in the seven days to 26 February, there were 51,447 new confirmed cases (91.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 February, there were 67,616 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (16,169 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 03 March is 3,674,028 (6,527.3 cases per 100,000 population).
